NAME		jlm
SYNTAX		jlm
		jlm add <module> <room>
		jlm remove <module>
		jlm reload
DESCRIPTION	The jlm command manipulates JeamLand Loadable Modules.
		Without arguments, it lists all loaded modules.
		The command can also be used to add and remove modules
		although to effect a permanent change, you will have to edit
		the file etc/modules.
		Jlm reload forces a load of any jlms listed in etc/modules
		which are not in memory.
